description.narrative:
The development impact of the project includes:
-   Introduce modern technologies which will enable LAPCO to produce better quality products at lower costs;
- Strengthen LAPCOs distribution centers in Central America leading to increased economies of scale and reduced negative impact of cyclicality.  
- Reduce market risk with a geographically diversified revenue stream;
- Grow the industrial base of the region and diversify the economy of the country;
- Create direct job opportunities, for about 240 direct employees, who will benefit from LAPCOs well developed staff compensation package including training and medical insurance schemes;   
- The plant construction project will generated around 500 indirect jobs;
- Introduce best practice environmental and social standards.
